div1.p: 137. Filed on the 11 day of October 1887.

In the District Court holding terms at Olympia
Petetion of Gus Bendjus Et al. for writ of Habeas Corpus
To George L Moody Prosecuting Attorney

Please take notice that a writ of Habeas Corpus has been issued to the Sheriff of Thurston County, commanding said Seriff to bring us the the bodies of the Bendjus et al before the Hon. Frank Allyn, judge of the Second Judicial District of Washington Territory that they may be discarged.
You will please appear & show cause to the contrary.
The writ is made returnable at Tacoma Court House at 10 o clock am Oct 13. 1887.
div1.ab: Reginold and Robinson Attorneys for Petetioners
div1.p: Service by copy accepted this 10 day of Oct at 8 o clock pm 1887
